# Task_NL - Component Documentation

This repository contains the implementation of a case study component built using **HTML** and **Tailwind CSS**. The task is part of a documentation request by Ingenius, providing a clean and functional layout for side navigation with design principles.

## Demo

![Preview](./icons/preview.png)

---

## Features

- **Responsive Sidebar**: Fully responsive layout with a collapsible sidebar.
- **Customizable Navigation Links**: Easy to update navigation items and icons.
- **Semantic HTML**: Ensures accessibility and search engine optimization.
- **Tailwind Integration**: Utilizes Tailwind CSS for rapid styling and utility-based classes.
- **Clean Design**: Minimalist design with hover effects and clear hierarchy.

---

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/wamblex/task-nl.git
   cd task-nl
   ```

2. Install dependencies:
   Make sure you have Tailwind CSS set up in your project. This example assumes you have already configured Tailwind.

3. Open index.html in your browser to view the component.

## File Structure

```bash
├── index.html # Main HTML file for the component
├── fonts.css # Font styles used in the design
├── output.css # Compiled Tailwind CSS file
├── icons/ # Directory containing icons used in the UI
├── InGenius Icon.svg # Company logo
└── README.md # Project documentation
```

Usage

## HTML Structure

The sidebar component is structured within an <aside> tag and contains navigation links grouped into sections:

```bash
<aside class="...">
  <nav>
    <a href="#">Reports</a>
    <a href="#">Programs</a>
    <!-- More links -->
  </nav>
</aside>
```

## Tailwind Utilities

This component uses the following Tailwind utilities:

    •	Flexbox for layout management
    •	Spacing utilities for padding and margins
    •	Colors and Opacity for hover effects and styling
    •	Border utilities for rounded corners and separators

## Customization

    1.	Update icons in the ./icons/ directory.
    2.	Modify text labels or links in the index.html file.
    3.	Update Tailwind configurations as needed in your tailwind.config.js.

Feel free to fork the repository and submit a pull request.
